result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason P. Warren was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While under Influence (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called: 8:37am. INCLUDES 10CF1, 09CM1361. Judge Brady; Court Reporter Kim Lentz; Clerk: Denise. State appears by ADA Laura Kohl. Defendant appears by phone. Atty Tim Osicka appears for Defendant. Probation Agent, Dawn Suza does not appear - State believed she would be present today. State makes statement re: matter today. Crt states he does not inform defendant when probation starts re: condition of probation. Atty Osicka requests EMP in Racine County. Court states that is the Probation Agent's recommendation in either Marathon County or Racine County- he does not override their discretion. Adjourned: 8:39am.

Case called: 9:20am. INCLUDES 09CM1361, 09CM1967, 10CM01, 10CF01. Judge Brady; Court Reporter Kim Lentz; Clerk: Denise.  State appears by ADA Laura Kohl. Def appears by Atty Tim Osicka. Parties have agreement to initial; plea & sentencing. Crt adjourns briefly on 9:23am. Back on the record @ 9:32am. Staet indicates ct 1 in 09CM1967 will be a felony (OWI 5th) therefore, State files Information on 10CF1. Waiver of Prelim. filed.  COURT questions defendant re: waiver; COURT finds waiver freely and vol. made, probable cause - defendant bound over for arraignment & trial.  Crt proceeds with Plea. *VRCW. Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights & Counsel filed.  State moves to DRI cts 2 (PAC) & ct 3 (OAR) 09CM1361 - crt grants. State moves to DRI 10CM1- crt grants. State moves to DRI cts 2, 3, 4 & 5 in 10CF1 - crt grants. PLEA: GUILTY  - ct 1 (OWI-4th) 09CM1361; ct 1 (OWI- 5th or greater) 10CF1. Crt advises def of rights & penalties & ques def to understanding.  Crt finds plea & waiver freely & vol made, a factual basis & def guilty. Crt informs & defendant signs Ineligible Voting Form. COURT ORDERS: 09CM1361 - 120 days MCJ with huber if eligible; Fine $1,496.00 inclusive of cc; 24 months dl revocation; AODA. COURT ORDERS: 10CF1 - Impose & Stay - WI State Prison for 6 years Total ; Initial Confinment of 3 yrs; Extended Supervision 3 yrs. Defendant placed on probation of 3 yrs. CONDITIONS: 1 yr jail with huber consecutive to 09CM1361; eligible for good time credit on both sentences; Fine $2,000; AODA; 35 months dl revo; concurrent; Immobiliation for one year; Driving with Care Program; Good faith effort to maintain employment; Counseling. Copy of CR 234 given to defendant. Atty Osicka requests EMP - crt does not object it is up to the jail. Atty Osicka makes statement re: probation and employment. Atty Osicka makes statement re: bond that was posted. Crt orders bond to be returned to bond poster.  Adjourned:  9:44am.
w/Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief (includes 09cm1967, filed in 09cm1361)

Case called: 3:00pm. INCLUDES 09CM1361, 09CM1967. Judge Brady; Court Reporter Donna DeBiase; Clerk: Denise. State appears by ADA Laura Kohl. Defendant appears by Atty Tim Osicka. Atty Osicka moves for bond modification. Arguments by State. Atty Osicka makes statement- was not aware of new OWI charges.  Crt denies bond modification. Adjourned: 3:08pm.
